txt.en: 'It has been a pleasure working with you, [placeholder].'
'All right, here we go. Keep an eye on that cave, and if any Orcs come running...well, you know what to do.'
Instance: Imminent Collapse
Ondor has been defeated
Ondor has collapsed the cave-entrance
You have died...
Defend Ondor as he works to collapse the cave-entrance.
Ondor is at the Orc-cave.\n\nYou should speak with Ondor the Dwarf once more.
Talk to Ondor
Defend Ondor
'How's it going there? Hold em off just a bit longer!'
Talk to Ondor at the Orc-cave
'Uh oh. Listen here [placeholder], this is gonna take a little longer than I thought.'
'Hold em off a little longer!'
'I dinna care how, just run around in circles or something!'
'Ack, he's a biggun ain't he? Well, here it goes!'
'That's done! Now for your little friend there...'
'I 'canna dig while I'm fighting! Give me a hand here!'

You have come upon a cave-entrance in the northern Heathfells, on the border of Nan Curunir, where you have encountered a rather unusual dwarf. Without heed to his own safety, he has set about collapsing the cave-entrance, which he claims leads to a warren of Orcs below.
'Back to work!'
'Hah! That's one more for the old Dwarf!'
'A'right, I'm ready to bring this thing down.'
'But there's gon' to be an awful racket.'
'Those Orcs are going to come running, and I'll need you to hold em off for a minute or two.'
'Here goes!'
'Well, I suppose that's the last of the Orcs. It will take them weeks to dig out that mess...lazy curs.\n\n'If it were dwarves trapped in there, they would be out in a day!'
